item.title: What the fuck? (Java)
item.dc:creator: @r0ckstar96 r0ckstar96
item.description:
@r0ckstar96 wrote:

I got a virus from Java in 2007. I used to be anti-Java and now I’m the total opposite. There was this orange coffee cup saying a new Java update was available and so I just decided to download it, after I clicked the little pop up bubble in my notification area of my screen, no download/install program came up. I clicked the bubble a few more times. Still nothing… I restart my computer. Everything is screwed up badly. No windows open, takes forever to log in to my admin account. Eventually I send out my computer to a lady who works with computers and fixes viruses. She told me it was a virus. She says the only way to get rid of it is to totally wipe my C drive. I was sad because it had lots of songs and good memories on there. I let her erase the drive. Saddest days of my life
